JNI, SDK, NDK are all a nightmare to work with.
Here's some help in case you get stuck trying to build it.

https://wiki.debian.org/AndroidTools
https://packages.debian.org/sid/devel/google-android-ndk-installer

Initial setup:
sudo apt install android-sdk android-sdk-platform-23 
sudo apt install google-android-ndk-installer
sudo apt install openjdk-8-jdk # (?)

# (?)
sudo apt install ia32-libs
sudo apt install libncurses5
sudo apt install ninja-build cmake

accepting sdk license:
https://wiki.debian.org/AndroidTools/IntroBuildingApps

`gradle build` may need to be run as sudo.